**[1848, 02-29] Ms.A.1.2.18.17**

Buffum, J.N., to RDW; Lynn.

He is so glad that Webb is a friend. “If I have one feeling stronger
than any other, it is love for friends who have been kind to me, and
especially those whose virtues comand [sic] my respect; and it grieves
me to feel that I am misunderstood by many, but it affords me pleasure
to know many do understand me so well.” Thinks he should come to the
United States and lecture on Ireland, especially to counteract similar
lectures by people like Clapp who just want to stir up national hatred.


